      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat(mxc): add Windows MXC sandbox backend",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\nOpenClaw does not currently have an official installable MXC sandbox backend for Windows hosts that can run sandboxed commands through Microsoft eXecution Containers. This leaves MXC-capable Windows environments without a first-party plugin path for ProcessContainer-backed execution and filesystem bridge operations.\n\n## Why This Change Was Made\n\nThis adds an official OpenShell-style external `mxc` sandbox plugin package (`@openclaw/mxc-sandbox`) with Windows-only readiness checks, plugin-owned MXC SDK dependency ownership, ProcessContainer payload construction, a plugin-side launcher, host-backed filesystem bridge support, sandbox policy loading, and targeted tests.\n\nThe plugin source lives under `extensions/mxc`, but it is packaged as an installable plugin (`bundledDist: false`) so the MXC SDK/native dependency is owned by the plugin package instead of an unshipped bundled `node_modules` tree. The backend uses the stable current MXC `0.7.0-alpha` schema and keeps sandbox defaults conservative: curated environments, headless UI, per-exec temp directories, absolute binary overrides, host-derived Windows roots, read-only default workspace access for `none`/`ro`, and fail-closed unsupported policy handling.\n\n## User Impact\n\nUsers on MXC-capable Windows hosts can install the official MXC sandbox plugin, restart the Gateway, configure `sandbox.backend: \"mxc\"`, and run OpenClaw sandboxed commands through MXC. Non-Windows or unsupported Windows hosts remain unaffected because the plugin stays dormant when readiness probes fail.\n\nInstall command:\n\n```bash\nopenclaw plugins install @openclaw/mxc-sandbox\n```\n\n## Evidence\n\n- `pnpm test:extension mxc -- --reporter=verbose` — passed.\n- `pnpm test extensions\\mxc test\\scripts\\generate-npm-shrinkwrap.test.ts -- --reporter=verbose` — passed.\n- `pnpm test:changed` — passed.\n- `pnpm release:plugins:npm:check -- --plugins @openclaw/mxc-sandbox` — passed; publishable plugin metadata looks OK.\n- `pnpm release:plugins:clawhub:check -- --plugins @openclaw/mxc-sandbox` — passed; publishable plugin metadata looks OK.\n- `pnpm check` — passed, including import cycle check with 0 runtime value cycles.\n- `pnpm build` — passed.\n- `node scripts\\lib\\plugin-npm-runtime-build.mjs extensions\\mxc` plus package-manifest `npm pack --dry-run` — passed; package includes `dist/index.js`, `dist/mxc-spawn-launcher.mjs`, and MXC SDK binaries including `node_modules/@microsoft/mxc-sdk/bin/x64/wxc-exec.exe`.\n- `pnpm deps:changes:report -- --base-ref origin/main --markdown <session>/dependency-changes.md --json <session>/dependency-changes.json` — generated dependency report.\n\nReal Windows MXC package proof:\n\n- Crabbox provider: `ssh`\n- Lease/id: `static_10-127-3-94`\n- Target: `windows-normal`\n- Remote Node/npm: `node v26.4.0`, `npm 11.17.0`\n- Built and packed `@openclaw/mxc-sandbox@2026.6.10` on the Windows host.\n- Installed published `openclaw@2026.6.10` plus the local packed plugin in a fresh temp project.\n- Verified package-owned runtime dependency path:\n  - `PROOF:installedOpenClaw=2026.6.10`\n  - `PROOF:installedPlugin=2026.6.10`\n  - `PROOF:mxcSdk=0.7.0`\n  - `PROOF:wxcExists=True ...\\node_modules\\@openclaw\\mxc-sandbox\\node_modules\\@microsoft\\mxc-sdk\\bin\\x64\\wxc-exec.exe`\n- Registered and ran backend `mxc`:\n  - `PROOF:registeredServices=mxc-sandbox-cleanup`\n  - `PROOF:backendId=mxc`\n  - sandbox command: `echo MXC_PROOF_OK && cd`\n  - `PROOF:exit=0`\n  - `PROOF:stdout=MXC_PROOF_OK |...\\workspace|`\n  - `PROOF:stderr=`\n\nUser-facing plugin install proof on the same Windows host:\n\n- Installed published `openclaw@2026.6.10` in an isolated temp project.\n- Ran `node <published-openclaw>/dist/entry.js plugins install <local @openclaw/mxc-sandbox tgz> --force --pin`.\n- Install succeeded:\n  - `PROOF3:installExit=0`\n  - install output included `Installing plugin dependencies…`, `Installed plugin: mxc`, and `Restart the gateway to load plugins.`\n  - `PROOF3:configExists=True`\n  - `PROOF3:configHasMxc=True`\n  - `PROOF3:pluginRoot=...\\state\\extensions\\mxc`\n  - `PROOF3:installedPlugin=2026.6.10`\n\nWorkspace access proof after review 4588711229:\n\n- Static SSH Windows host: `provider=ssh`, lease `static_10-127-3-94`, target `windows-normal`.\n- `workspaceAccess: \"none\"` now keeps the MXC workdir read-only rather than read-write by default:\n  - `PROOF4:backendId=mxc`\n  - `PROOF4:workspaceAccess=none`\n  - `PROOF4:workdirReadonly=true`\n  - `PROOF4:workdirReadwrite=false`\n- Command execution still succeeds with the read-only default workspace policy:\n  - sandbox command: `echo MXC_NONE_PROOF_OK && cd`\n  - `PROOF4:exit=0`\n  - `PROOF4:stdout=MXC_NONE_PROOF_OK |...\\workspace|`\n  - `PROOF4:stderr=`\n\nFull `pnpm test` was attempted earlier per CONTRIBUTING, but the broad local suite hit unrelated existing non-MXC failures in UI/TUI/agent runtime tests before completion. The changed/MXC-specific lanes above passed cleanly.\n\nCopilot autoreview was attempted on the latest review-fix head. It produced a finding about `@microsoft/mxc-sdk@0.7.0` re-serializing config into `--config-base64` for `wxc-exec`; local source inspection confirmed that this is the current upstream SDK transport behavior and that the SDK exposes no non-argv transport for `spawnSandboxFromConfig`. No local OpenClaw-only patch is available without an upstream SDK/executor transport change.\n\n## Notes\n\n- Contributor changelog edit was removed per CONTRIBUTING.\n- `.github/labeler.yml` maps `extensions/mxc/**` to `plugin: mxc`.\n- Upstream label verification found no existing `plugin: mxc` label; label creation requires maintainer permissions.\n- Dependency Graph Guard still requires maintainer/security `/allow-dependencies-change` approval for the current head SHA 7dc546ccb7ffc27830bbe1c932f58640662c52c7.\r\n",
